org.tsugi

Interface Launch

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseLaunch

    public interface Launch
    This captures all of the data associated with the LTI Launch.

      • isComplete

        boolean isComplete()
        Indicate if this request is completely handled This is used as follows: 
        
      public void doPost (...)
      Launch launch = tsugi.getLaunch(req, res);
      if ( launch.isComplete() ) return;
        This allows the Tsugi framework to do things like redirect back to itself.

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Indicate if this request is valid This fails if the LTI Launch was malformed or the session data is corrupted.

      • getGetUrl

        String getGetUrl(String path)
        Get a GET URL to the current servlet We abstract this in case the framework needs to point to a URL other than the URL in the request object. This URL should be used for AJAX calls to dynamic data in JavaScript.

      • getPostUrl

      • getHidden

        String getHidden()
        Get any needed hidden form fields This will be properly formatted HTML - most likely one or more input type="hidden" fields - the framework may use this to help it maintain context across request / response cycles.
        Returns:
        String Text to include in a form. May be the empty string if nothing is needed by the framework.
